Here's how to handle all three requirements:

**1 & 2. Intercept back navigation + confirm dialog**

Override `OnBackButtonPressed` in your page code-behind:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Fire-and-forget since the override is synchronous
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () =>
            {
                bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                    "Unsaved Changes",
                    "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                    "Discard", "Stay");

                if (leave)
                {
                    _hasUnsavedChanges = false;
                    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
                }
            });

            return true; // cancel the default navigation
        }

        return base.OnBackButtonPressed(); // allow normal back
    }
}
```

> **Note:** `OnBackButtonPressed` handles the **hardware/Android back button**. It does **not** fire when the user taps the Shell navigation bar's back arrow — that requires `BackButtonBehavior` (below).

**3. Custom "Cancel" back button with the same guard**

In your XAML, replace the default back arrow:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior
            TextOverride="Cancel"
            Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

Then expose the command (code-behind or ViewModel):

```csharp
public ICommand BackCommand { get; }

public EditProductPage()
{
    InitializeComponent();

    BackCommand = new Command(async () =>
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave) return;
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    });

    BindingContext = this;
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`OnBackButtonPressed`** → guards the Android/hardware back button; return `true` to cancel.
- **`BackButtonBehavior`** → guards (and customizes) the Shell toolbar back button; `TextOverride` replaces the arrow with "Cancel".
- Both paths need the guard because they fire independently.
- Set `_hasUnsavedChanges = true` whenever a form field changes (e.g., via `TextChanged` events or ViewModel property setters).
